<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bow1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bow,</orth> subst. 1) instrument to shoot arrows: <bibl n="shak. ven 581" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 581</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 580" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 580</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 24</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.355" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 355</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.1.126" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.249" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 249</bibl>. <cit><quote>To bend a b.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 9</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 116</bibl>. <cit><quote>draw your b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 2, 47</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 88</bibl>. <cit><quote>a' drew a good b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 48</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the b. is bent and drawn,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 145</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) rainbow: <cit><quote>thy blue b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 80</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>heavenly b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 80</bibl></cit>
<lb />3) yoke: <cit><quote>as the ox hath his b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 80</bibl></cit>.
